HEADWORD: Homocercal
<hw>Ho`mo*cer"cal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Homo-</ets> + Gr. <?/ tail.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having the tail nearly or quite symmetrical, the vertebral column
terminating near its base; -- opposed to
<xex>heterocercal</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

